Here's the complete implementation:

**Configure size limits in `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
// Configure form options to enforce the 10 MB limit
builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(options =>
{
    options.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10 MB
});

// If using Kestrel, also set the request body limit
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(options =>
{
    options.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 10 * 1024 * 1024;
});
```

**Add the endpoint (after `var app = builder.Build();`):**

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file) =>
{
    // Validate content type
    string[] allowed = ["image/jpeg", "image/png"];
    if (!allowed.Contains(file.ContentType))
        return Results.BadRequest("Only JPEG and PNG files are allowed.");

    // Validate size (defense-in-depth alongside FormOptions limit)
    const long maxSize = 10 * 1024 * 1024;
    if (file.Length > maxSize)
        return Results.BadRequest("File exceeds the 10 MB limit.");

    // Ensure uploads directory exists
    var uploadsPath = Path.Combine(app.Environment.ContentRootPath, "uploads");
    Directory.CreateDirectory(uploadsPath);

    // Generate a safe, unique filename preserving the original extension
    var ext = Path.GetExtension(file.FileName).ToLowerInvariant();
    if (ext is not ".jpg" and not ".jpeg" and not ".png")
        return Results.BadRequest("Invalid file extension.");

    var fileName = $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{ext}";
    var filePath = Path.Combine(uploadsPath, fileName);

    await using var stream = File.Create(filePath);
    await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

    return Results.Ok(new { fileName });
})
.DisableAntiforgery(); // Required for non-browser API clients
```

**Key points:**

- **`DisableAntiforgery()`** — since your pipeline has `UseAntiforgery()`, API file uploads from non-browser clients (Postman, mobile apps) will fail without this. If uploads come from Razor/Blazor forms, remove this and send the antiforgery token instead.
- **Double validation** — `FormOptions` rejects oversized requests at the framework level (returns 400 automatically); the in-handler check is defense-in-depth.
- **`Guid` filename** — prevents path traversal and overwrites from user-supplied names.
- **Extension + content type** — both are checked since content type alone can be spoofed.
